Usage
        base-convert base... number
        base-convert base... -a number...
        base-convert -i [base1 base2 number]
        base-convert --help

                             : --------------------------------------------------

Description
        Convert numbers from one base representation to another.

Arguments
        base1                : Serve as the initial base for the number.
        base2                : The base the number will converts into.
        base...              : Bases the number will converts into. Where the
                               first base serve as the initial base.
        number...            : Numbers to be converted to the other bases. 
                               These must be written in the representation of the
                               initial base.

Options
        -i,                  : Use an interactive prompts to insert values.
        --interactive          When an input stream is entered incorrectly, this
                               will trigger the entry to be re-entered in the
                               proper form.
                               Initial value for each prompts can be given.
        -a, --array          : Provide multiple numbers for conversions.
        -h, --help           : Show this help file.

Examples
                base-convert 36 16 10 8 2 pickle
        Show the representation of the number 'pickle' from base36 into base16,
        base10, base8 and base2.

                base-convert --interactive
        Run in interactive mode, where number, base1 and base2 will be prompted
        for entry.

                base-convert -i 2 10 1010010001010101
        Run in interactive mode. With supplied initial values, if no errors were
        encountered, no prompts will be given.

                base-convert 36 16 10 8 2 -a omae wa mou shindeiru
        Show the representation of each numbers 'omae', 'wa', 'mou' and
        'shindeiru' from base36 into base16, base10, base8 and base2.
